for the and that's not
even counting the extremely

00:26:13.170 --> 00:26:17.540
privileged, this just is that
broader top of the society,

00:26:17.540 --> 00:26:22.120
have been able to pass
along their advantages more

00:26:22.120 --> 00:26:27.380
efficiently to their kids than
earlier upper-classes have been

00:26:27.380 --> 00:26:30.360
and actually I discovered
Richard quoted something I said

00:26:30.360 --> 00:26:33.840
over lunch in a book and
thank God he's a friend,

00:26:33.840 --> 00:26:36.900
because he quoted something I
kind of liked to repeat instead

00:26:36.900 --> 00:26:40.000
of some damn fool
thing I said over lunch

00:26:40.000 --> 00:26:41.710
of which there were
many, but you know,

00:26:41.710 --> 00:26:44.430
I said that I spend my weeks
writing columns announcing

00:26:44.430 --> 00:26:46.940
inequality and my nights
and weekends increasing it.

00:26:46.940 --> 00:26:50.750
You know, because as
somebody who is effectively

00:26:50.750 --> 00:26:53.530
in the upper middle-class
whatever class I'm in somewhere

00:26:53.530 --> 00:26:56.900
up there, I have an opportunity
to pass along benefits

00:26:56.900 --> 00:27:00.830
to my kids, you know, for no
particular virtue of mine,

00:27:00.830 --> 00:27:03.400
just because I happen to
be here and I am going

00:27:03.400 --> 00:27:06.480
to do whatever I can to help
my kids as all of us will do,

00:27:06.480 --> 00:27:08.440
but those kind of, you know,

00:27:08.440 --> 00:27:11.080
the way in which
those advantages kind

00:27:11.080 --> 00:27:14.100
of bundle together we
have less social mobility.

00:27:14.100 --> 00:27:16.730
Second thing is,
we have had less,

00:27:16.730 --> 00:27:23.000
a far less equally distributed
income growth that in the sort

00:27:23.000 --> 00:27:27.130
of great period from World
War II through the mid70s,

00:27:27.130 --> 00:27:31.250
1980 each quintile tended
to go up roughly equally.

00:27:31.250 --> 00:27:33.900
We had not only a great
period of economic growth,

00:27:33.900 --> 00:27:36.700
but a great period of
shared economic growth.

00:27:36.700 --> 00:27:41.520
Since then, we have, it
has not been shared at all

00:27:41.520 --> 00:27:44.760
that the middle and bottom
have stagnated and a lot

00:27:44.760 --> 00:27:47.020
of the benefits have gone
to the top and especially

00:27:47.020 --> 00:27:51.260
to the very top, and
what we're discovering,

00:27:51.260 --> 00:27:54.790
and this is I think a question
